Change a Swarm Record's Slack Channel Name

When a swarm record is created in Salesforce, the swarm record's name appears in the Collaboration Room field. If the Slack channel name contains sensitive information, consider changing the name in Slack or updating the Collaboration Room field. You can also choose to hide the Collaboration Room field from certain users.

To change a Swarm Record's Slack Channel Name:

Open the swarm record in Salesforce.
Select the Collaboration Room.
Under Room Name, select Edit.
Enter a new name that doesnâ€™t contain sensitive information.
Save your changes.
title: Change Slack Channel Name in Service Cloud Swarm Records
